    <name>Assignment #3: Explore Research on SCL and Relate it to Writing Instruction</name>
    <intro>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;" size="3"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;Explore the research behind student-centered learning and motivation and consider how you can apply what you learn to writing instruction. Spend more time learning about student-centered learning with these two sources:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;A NCSALL Focus on Basics publication: &lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;a title="The First Three Weeks: A Critical Time for Motivation" href="http://www.ncsall.net/index.php@id=420.html" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana;" size="3" face="Verdana"&gt;The First Three Weeks: A Critical Time for Motivation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;, by B. Allan Quigley&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;Selected Readings from Jobs for the Future publication: &lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;a title="PDF - opens in new window  - Motivation, Engagement, and Student Voice" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Pages%20from%20MotivationEngagementStudentVoice_fullpage.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana;" face="Verdana"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Motivation, Engagement, and Student Voice&lt;/em&gt; (pages 23-34)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;:  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;em&gt;How Student Voice Can Elevate Motivation and Engagement&lt;/em&gt; (pages 23-29); &lt;em&gt;Why Student Voice is Student-Centered Learning&lt;/em&gt; (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;pages 30-32); and &lt;em&gt;Conclusion&lt;/em&gt; (pages 33-34) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span size="3" face="Calibri"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;Write a one-page reflection of how you can put students at the center of writing instruction and activities. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;Click below on "Add my submission" to submit your reflection &lt;span size="4" face="Trebuchet MS"&gt;or copy and paste your reflection into the online text box&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
